parameters: \n<Soldier>"It was a long way here, but I'm glad it was an easy job."

\n<Soldier a>"Ahh, this booze is really easy to drink! I might get drunk
pretty quickly."

\n<Soldier b>"Really. Ah, if only we had some good snacks to go with it,
no complaints then. It's damp out here."
The soldiers straightened up and saluted.
\n<Soldier a>"What can we do for you?"

\n<Roselitte>"Where did that alcohol come from? Are you carrying alcohol
on an expedition mission?"

\n<Roselitte>"...Surely you aren't just helping yourselves to the
village's supplies, are you?"

\n<Soldier a>"No, absolutely not! This alcohol was provided by the
courtesy of His Highness the Crown Prince!"
\n<Roselitte>"...What did you say? The Crown Prince's?"

\n<Soldier b>"Yes. He said since he brought the alcohol, we should drink
it, and he was going around offering it to the soldiers."

\n<Roselitte>"I hate to be a wet blanket--as much as I'd like to say
otherwise, we are still on duty. Even if it's from His
Highness, please remember to behave with moderation."

\n<Soldier>"Th-thank you for your hard work, Roselitte-sama. Would you
like to warm up a bit?"
\n<Soldier>"On a cold night, there's nothing better than a drink!"

\n<Soldier>"Hehehe... Everything has gone according to my plan so
far...!"
\n<Soldier>"Ugh, what the hell is this shitty hand!"
\n<Soldier b>"Seriously?! Damn it, you win again?"

\n<Soldier a>"Hahaha! Okay, let's have another round! You must be
frustrated losing like this, right?"
\n<Roselitte>"...What is all this noise about? It's quite loud."
\n<Soldier a>"What? We were just at the good part--"

\n<Roselitte>"...It's fine. Now, what have you been making noise about
since earlier?"
\n<Soldier a>"Well... we were playing a game."

\n<Soldier a>"Yes. It's a card game where you arrange these cards with
symbols and numbers into stronger combinations."
\n<Soldier a>"How about it, Lady Roselitte? It's quite fun, you know."
\n<Roselitte>"...No, thank you. I don't even know the rules."

\n<Soldier b>"Oh, that's perfect. Actually, this guy is incredibly strong
at this game. He often teaches various people while
playing."

\n<Soldier b>"His skills are reputed to be the strongest in the empire.
He makes the game really interesting, so you should
definitely give it a try!"
\n<Roselitte>"...The strongest in the empire, you say."

\n<Soldier a>"Well, that might be an exaggeration... but I do have
confidence! Even against Lady Roselitte, I won't back down
on this!"
\n<Soldier c>"Wow, he's saying such things to Lady Roselitte..."

\n<Soldier d>"Lady Roselitte! How about a match? Please take revenge for
us!"
\n<Soldier a>"Of course! So, first you take these cards--"
\n<Soldier b>"Whoa, amazing! Lady Roselitte won again!"
\n<Soldier a>"Tch... Too strong... And I had such a good hand too...!"

\n<Roselitte>"Hmph. All that boasting and this is all you've got? To
claim to be the strongest in the empire is laughable."

\n<Soldier a>"Grr...! Lady Roselitte, one more match! This time I
definitely won't lose!"
\n<Roselitte>"Very well. But I won't go easy on you next time either--"
\n<Roselitte>"...Ahem. That's enough for now. I will take my leave."

\n<Soldier a>"But we were just getting to the good part! Let's play a
little longer. You were enjoying it, weren't you?"
\n<Roselitte>"...Not particularly. It was just average. Average."

\n<Roselitte>"It's already night, so try not to be too noisy.
Understood?"

\n<Soldier a>"...Yes, Lady Roselitte. If there's another chance, please
let us invite you again."

parameters.name: ドアノブ（がちゃがちゃ）02

parameters:
\n<Ameria>"Yeah, that should do it! If you're still in pain anywhere,
just let me know!"

\n<Villager A>"Wow... The wounds I got from the bandits have vanished like
magic! Thank you, Ameria-chan!"

\n<Ameria>"Next, please!... A leg injury, huh. Don't worry, it'll heal
up quickly!"

\n<Villager B>"Ameria-chan, I had no idea you were so skilled with healing
arts. Medicine and healing arts make such a difference in
treatment, we're lucky to have you."

\n<Villager C>"But you've heard, haven't you? This commotion was all
because Ameria-chan..."

\n<Villager B>"Yeah, well, that's true but the girl's not to blame. You
got your wounds treated by her too, so don't say things like
that."
Ameria is focused on the treatment.
\n<Villager>"Ouch... I got punched really hard by those bandits."

\n<Villager>"I sprained my ankle while trying to escape. It's such a
nuisance, really."

\n<Villager>"I was surprised to be attacked, but I'm glad it was only to
this extent."
\n<Villager>"Really, if only the Imperial Army had come sooner..."
\n<Villager>"I'm so grateful that Ameria-chan was here to help."
\n<Villager>"She's more skilled than the army's medics, that girl."

\n<Villager>"Ah, my back hurts because I moved too suddenly... I wish
Ameria-chan could take a look at it soon..."

\n<Soldier>"The army's medical officer is conducting examinations over
there. Shall we go and have a look?"

\n<Villager>"See, I told you so. That's why we should have stopped it
back then."

\n<Villager>"Can't be helped. Even soldiers have no choice but to follow
orders."

\n<Villager>"Fortunately, there were no fatalities, but I'm worried
about those who fled outside the village. I hope they remain
safe until morning..."

\n<Villager>"Look, look. I got it treated by a healer from the Tekoku
army over there. I scraped my knee."

\n<Villager>"I was certain that our village had been abandoned by the
lord... But perhaps there is some reason behind it."

\n<Imperial army medical officer>"I've been making rounds to check on the situation, but it
seems safe to leave this place in her hands. It's a relief
to have such a skilled medic here."
